    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.8.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 13.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niterm2 v3.4.18\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n``` zsh\r\nnvim\r\n\r\n:q\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI hope nothing happens to my iTerm configuration.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nI have configured my iTerm2 with a _**blinking vertical bar**_ cursor.\r\n\r\nHowever, when I open and quit `nvim`, the cursor will be changed back to an _**unblinking box style**_. \r\nMore worse, it cannot be re-configured through iTerm2 preference even I quit and reopen iTerm2, unless I close and open a new iTerm2 window.\r\n\r\nI have tried vim on my Mac and nothing like that happens.",
