            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@dreistein543 I use this:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.cmd([[\r\n    augroup RestoreCursorShapeOnExit\r\n        autocmd!\r\n        autocmd VimLeave * set guicursor=a:ver1\r\n    augroup END\r\n]])\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis works for me with Alacritty terminal and GNOME terminal, with kitty terminal it's not necessary, kitty keeps the shape of the cursor.\r\n\r\n@zeertzjq  Vim doesn't change the shape of the cursor, why does Neovim?",
